<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<sect1 id="description">
<title>Description</title>

<para>KCron is an application for scheduling programs to run in the background.
It is a graphical user interface to cron, the Unix system scheduler.</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="acknowledgements">
<title>Acknowledgements</title>

<para>KCron was initially based upon kcrontab developed by 
<ulink url="mailto:michael@quinto.ruhr.de">Michael Bialas</ulink>
and documented by
<ulink url="mailto:klemm@abacus.at">David Klemm</ulink>.</para>

<para>KCron acknowledges 
<ulink url="mailto:paul@vix.com">Paul Vixie</ulink> for vixie-cron.</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="license">
<title>License</title>

